  "commentary": "ABOUT [ edit ]\n\nState Bank of India is a Fortune 500 company. It is an Indian Multinational, Public Sector banking and financial services statutory body headquartered in Mumbai. It is the largest and oldest bank in India with over 200 years of history.[1]\n\nKEY POINTS [ edit ]\n\nMarket Share[1]\nAs of Q3 FY26, the bank has a deposit market share of about 22% and a net advance share of 20% in India.\n\nBusiness Segments\nRetail Banking: 36% in Q3 FY26 vs 35% in FY23\nCorporate Banking: 21% in Q3 FY26 vs 21% in FY23\nTreasury Operations: 18% in Q3 FY26 vs 22% in FY23\nInsurance Business: 21% in Q3 FY26 vs 18% in FY23\nOthers: 5% in Q3 FY26 vs 4% in FY23 [2][3]\n\nKey Ratios\nNIM: 3.12% in Q3 FY26 vs 3.39% in FY23\nCRAR: 14.04% in Q3 FY26 vs 14.68% in FY23\nGNPA: 1.57% in Q3 FY26 vs 2.78% in FY23\nNNPA: 0.39% in Q3 FY26 vs 0.67% in FY23\nPCR: 75.54% in Q3 FY26 vs 76.39% in FY23\nSlippage Ratio: 7% in Q3 FY26 vs 0.65% in FY23 [4][5]\n\nDomestic Branch Network\nBranches ('000): 23.13 in Q3 FY26 vs 22.41 in FY23\nBC Outlets ('000): 79.6 in Q3 FY26 vs 76.1 in FY23\nATMs ('000): 63 in Q3 FY26 vs 65.6 in FY23 [6][7][8]\n\nInternational Presence\nThe company operates 241 overseas offices across 29 countries, including Canada, Brazil, Russia, Germany, France, Turkey, etc. [9] The international business accounted for 15% of the total advances and 4% of the total deposits in Q3 FY26.[10][11]\n\nLoan Book[10]\nAs of Q3 FY26, the bank has advances of Rs. 46,83,508 Cr vs Rs. 40,67,752 Cr in Q3 FY25.\nDomestic Advance Mix:\nRetail: 42%\nCorporate: 33%\nSME: 15%\nAgri: 10%\n\nDeposits[11]\nAs of Q3 FY26, the company has total deposits of Rs. 57,01,309 Cr vs Rs. 52,29,384 Cr in Q3 FY25.\nDomestic Deposits Mix:\nTerm Deposits: 61%\nCASA: 39%\n\nFinancial Inclusion[12]\nThe bank promotes financial inclusion through 79,630 Business Correspondent (BC) outlets, processing 3.27 Lac Cr transactions worth Rs. 58.68 Cr. Deposits in Financial Inclusion (FI) accounts increased to Rs. 82,350 Cr across 4,475 Cr accounts. The bank holds the largest market share among PSBs in social security schemes, with 46.83% in PMJJBY, 39.40% in PMSBY, and 32.14% in APY as of Q3 FY26.\n\nDigital Initiatives[13][14]\nThe bank offers digital services via WhatsApp banking, digital loans, cross-selling products, and a payment ecosystem featuring QR codes, POS machines, and online credit facilities. Alternate channels like Internet, Mobile, UPI, and YONO account for 94% of its transactions, securing a 24.78% market share in UPI remittances. It processed 1,562 Cr UPI transactions, registered ~88 Lac YONO users, and disbursed 2.2 lakh digital loans in Q3 FY26.\n\nSubsidiaries\n1) SBI Life Insurance: Leadership in the private market with a 28.1% Individual New Business Premium market share.\n2) SBI Card: No.2 player in Cards with 218 lakh cards in force and No.3 in Spends.[15]\n3) SBI Fund: As of Q3 FY26, SBIFML has a quarterly Average AUM of \u20b9 12.49 Lakh Cr with a market share of 15.42%.\n4) SBI General: Ranked 7th amongst the Private players in 9MFY26 with a market share of 6.64%.\n5) SBI Cap: Ranked No.1 for Debt Private placement of bonds in 9MFY26 with market share of ~35%.[16]\n\nIPO of SBI Funds[17]\nThe bank\u2019s Executive Committee has approved divestment of 6.30% stake (3.21 crore equity shares) in SBI Funds Management Ltd via an IPO, subject to regulatory approvals. The transaction is aimed at partial monetization of its asset management subsidiary while retaining majority control, and is expected to enhance transparency, unlock value, and support capital optimization.\n\nAcquisition[18]\nBank\u2019s Executive Committee has approved divestment of 6.30% stake (3.21 crore equity shares) in SBI Funds Management Ltd via an IPO, subject to regulatory approvals. The transaction is aimed at partial monetization of its asset management subsidiary while retaining majority control, and is expected to enhance transparency, unlock value, and support capital optimization.\n\nFocus[19]\nThe bank expects a loan book growth of 13% to 15% in FY27 revised from 12% to 14%.\n\nLast edited 1\u00a0month, 4\u00a0weeks ago\n Request an update \n\n\u00a9 Protected by Copyright",
